-- Factbox: List of investors BofA agreed to settle with
-- 
-- Wed Jun 29, 2011 8:16am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/29/us-bankofamerica-settlement-fb-idUSTRE75S2PZ20110629

 

 Bank of America Corp settled nearly all of the claims related to the legacy Countrywide-issued first-lien residential mortgage-backed securitization (RMBS) repurchase exposure for $8.5 billion in cash. 

 Here is the list of the 22 investors with whom Bank of America agreed to settle with: * AEGON USA Investment Management * Bayerische Landesbank * BlackRock Financial Management * Federal Home Loan Bank of Atlanta * Federal Reserve Bank of New York's Maiden Lane entities * Goldman Sachs Asset Management * ING Investment Management * ING Bank fsb. * ING Capital * Invesco Advisers * Kore Advisors * Landesbank Baden-Wuerttemberg and LBBW Asset Management (Ireland) * Metropolitan Life Insurance Co * Nationwide Mutual Insurance Company and its affiliates * Neuberger Berman Europe Ltd * New York Life Investment Management * Pacific Investment Management Co (PIMCO) * Prudential Investment Management * Teachers Insurance and Annuity Association of America * Thrivent Financial for Lutherans * Trust Company of the West and its affiliates controlled by The TCW Group * Western Asset Management Co (Compiled by Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore)